Every .c file here represents a r0ket firmware.
(additional source files may be in a subdirectory with the same name)

Call make as "make APP=filename" to build one.

Default filename is "final", the official r0ket firmware.

Have fun.

Addition 2017DEC15:

To set up the path to the CodeSourcery compiler,
source ~/scripts/sourceSourcery

where sourceSourcery:
export PATH=$PATH:/home/cmaier/CCC2011/r0ket/CodeSourcery/Sourcery_G++_Lite/bin

To flash:
r0ket/firmware$ gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.media-handling automount false
r0ket/firmware$ gsettings get org.gnome.desktop.media-handling automount
false

r0ket/firmware$ make flash APP=mist

r0ket/firmware$ gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.media-handling automount true
r0ket/firmware$ gsettings get org.gnome.desktop.media-handling automount
true
